      "file_path": "kubernetes/policy/components/policy-clamp-be/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 90,
      "message": "So just to make sure that I understand this properly.\nThose are credentials which will be used by this component to access cl-runtime (other clamp component) right?\nIf that's the case then it cannot be merged as is. You need to define a secret using common secret template in the \"server component\" and then pass it using parent component as externalSecret to here instead of hardcoding those passwords everywhere.\nYou can take a look how cps is doing that as it's a very recent example how to do it properly",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4965,
        "name": "Krzysztof Opasiak",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "k.opasiak@samsung.com",
        "username": "kopasiak"
      },
      "updated": "2021-09-23 15:51:41.000000000",
